dsslive.org


o /boot
	contains the initramfs, isolinux configuration files and kernel

o /deb
	If .deb (debian packages) are placed in this directory, they will
	be installed at boot time.

COMPRESSED FILES

o /base
	contains base, a minimal console system compressed in a squashfs image

o /xserver
	contains modules with X server applications.

o /deliver
	contains the scripts that allow the pure debian/ubuntu system to
	boot-up from cdrom

o /kernel
	contains the "/lib/modules/`uname -r`/" directory and the kernel
	related utilities


